---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, '/');
---
<section id="tech-writing" aria-label="Technical Writing and Developer Portal" class="section">

  <div class="sec-body-grid">
    <div class="sec-left">

      <div class="sec-meta">
        <span class="sec-date">2019 — 2023</span>
        <span class="sec-company">VTEX</span>
        <span class="sec-industry">E-commerce · SaaS</span>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-q">"How does tech work?"</p>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Technical Writing</h2>
      <p class="sec-sub">From API documentation to leading a team — building the developer portal that beat Spotify.</p>

      <div class="sec-stats">
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">35K+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">developers · 80+ countries</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">50+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">REST API endpoints documented</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">100+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">help centre articles</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">4</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">writers managed</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-text">Fresh out of a business degree with no technical background, I was drawn to tech writing because it allowed me to understand how technology worked. What I didn't expect was that not knowing things would turn out to be the job skill. The best technical documentation starts where the reader starts: at the beginning, with honest questions. I happened to be genuinely at the beginning, which meant I asked engineers things no one else thought to ask (bless them for the patience), and wrote docs that actually answered them. From my first internship in tech to actually leading a team of tech writers, four years of working with documentation built something most PMMs don't have: a working mental model of how products are built, not just sold.</p>
      <div class="sec-links">
        <a href="https://devportalawards.org/nominees/2023/vtex" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DevPortal Awards 2023 — Best Interface ↗</a>
        <a href="https://developers.vtex.com" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">VTEX Developer Portal ↗</a>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="sec-panels">
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Skills</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill">API Documentation</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">REST API Guides</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">SDK Documentation</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">UI/UX Writing</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Developer Experience (DevEx)</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Content Architecture</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Information Architecture</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Documentation Strategy</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Team Leadership</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Technical Training</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">UX Writing Guidelines</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Tools &amp; Languages</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">OpenAPI / Swagger 3.0</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">GitHub</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Markdown</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">HTML</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">CSS</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">JSON</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Google Apps Script</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Zapier</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">VSCode</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case card row — full width below the 2-col grid -->
  <div class="sec-cases-row sec-cases-row--single">
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-img">
        <img src={`${base}images/cases/vtex-dev-portal.gif`} alt="VTEX Developer Portal" />
      </div>
      <div class="sec-case-type">Developer portal · Award winner</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">VTEX Developer Portal</h3>
      <p class="sec-case-desc">50+ REST API endpoints, 30+ integration guides. 35K+ monthly developers. Winner of DevPortal Award 2023 — Best Interface alongside Spotify, Miro, and Mercedes-Benz.</p>
      <a href="https://devportalawards.org/nominees/2023/vtex" class="sec-case-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View award ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
